Printing Stars '*' in Pyramid Shape

Input Format

Read n value

Constraints

1<=n<=10^7

Output Format

Printing Stars '*' in Pyramid Shape

Sample Input 0

5
Sample Output 0

    * 
   * * 
  * * * 
 * * * * 
* * * * * 
Sample Input 1

10
Sample Output 1

         * 
        * * 
       * * * 
      * * * * 
     * * * * * 
    * * * * * * 
   * * * * * * * 
  * * * * * * * * 
 * * * * * * * * * 
* * * * * * * * * * 
//source code
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int n;
    scanf("%d",&n);
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= (n - i); j++) {
                printf(" ");
            }
            for (int k = 1; k <= i; k++) {
                printf("* ");
            }
            printf("\n");
        }
    return 0;
}
